<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n54104k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n54" href="#n54104k">N54 (VI.B.45)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n54all.htm#n54104k"> 104(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> nurse Halimah</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">It was the custom in Meccah to give young children into the care of Bedouin women, thus sending them away from the hot and dusty city into the pure air of the desert. The little Mohammed was <mark>nursed by a woman named Halimah</mark> of the tribe of Banu Saad, and the first five years of his life were spent in the tents of this wandering tribe. <small> Edith Holland, <a name="EHSM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#EHSM"><cite title="source">The Story of Mohammed</cite></a> (1914) 31</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
